## 1. Repository Layout

The project is split across three GitHub repositories under the `VastraCo-AWS` organization:

| Repository | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `VastraCo-AWS/vastraCo-app` | Application source code — all five microservices and the CI workflow |
| `VastraCo-AWS/vastraCo-helm` | Helm chart, ArgoCD Application/AppProject manifests, kgateway routing |
| `VastraCo-AWS/vastraCo-terraform` | Terraform modules for all AWS infrastructure |

### vastraCo-app structure

```
vastraCo-app/
├── .github/
│   └── workflows/
│       ├── ci.yml          # Build, scan, and push all services
│       └── cd.yml          # GitOps Helm update + ArgoCD sync verification
├── frontend/               # React + Vite SPA (port 80 in container)
├── user-service/           # Node.js auth service (port 3001)
├── product-service/        # Node.js product catalog (port 3002)
├── order-service/          # Node.js order management (port 3003)
├── ai-service/             # Python FastAPI + LangGraph agent (port 3004)
├── docker-compose.yml      # Local development stack
├── .env.example            # Environment variable template
└── README.md
```

### vastraCo-helm structure

```
vastraCo-helm/
├── argocd/
│   ├── application-production.yaml   # ArgoCD Application (auto-sync, self-heal)
│   ├── application-kgateway.yaml     # Gateway API route application
│   └── appproject.yaml               # ArgoCD AppProject with RBAC
├── charts/
│   └── vastraco-services/
│       ├── Chart.yaml
│       ├── values.yaml               # Default values for all services
│       ├── values-production.yaml    # Production overrides (image tags, IRSA ARNs)
│       └── templates/
│           ├── _helpers.tpl
│           ├── configmap.yaml
│           ├── deployment.yaml       # Single template iterating all services
│           ├── hpa.yaml
│           ├── namespace.yaml
│           ├── networkpolicy.yaml
│           ├── secretproviderclass.yaml
│           ├── service.yaml
│           └── serviceaccount.yaml
├── jobs/
│   └── db-creation-job.yaml
└── kgateway/
    ├── gateway.yaml
    └── httproute.yaml
```

### vastraCo-terraform structure

```
vastraCo-terraform/
├── bootstrap/              # One-time state bucket and OIDC setup
├── scripts/
│   ├── setup-aws-oidc.sh   # Wire up GitHub OIDC with AWS
│   └── setup-github.sh     # Set GitHub secrets/vars for CI
└── terraform/
    ├── main.tf             # Root module — composes all sub-modules
    ├── variables.tf
    ├── outputs.tf
    ├── providers.tf
    ├── versions.tf
    ├── locals.tf
    ├── terraform.tfvars
    └── modules/
        ├── vpc/            # VPC, subnets, NAT gateways, route tables
        ├── eks/            # EKS cluster, managed node group, OIDC
        ├── rds/            # PostgreSQL 16, subnet group, security group
        ├── kms/            # Customer Managed Key for all encryption
        ├── secretsmanager/ # db-creds, jwt-secret, app-secrets secrets
        ├── irsa/           # OIDC provider + per-service IAM roles
        ├── iam/            # EKS cluster role, node role
        ├── s3/             # Product images bucket with OAC
        ├── alb/            # Application Load Balancer (HTTPS termination)
        ├── cloudfront/     # CDN distribution (WAF-protected)
        ├── waf/            # WAF v2 WebACL with AWS managed rule sets
        ├── route53/        # DNS (vastraco.online)
        └── monitoring/     # CloudWatch log groups, alarms, SNS alerts
```

