## 3. Application Services

### 3.1 Frontend

| Item | Detail |
|---|---|
| Technology | React 18 + Vite, Tailwind CSS |
| Container | nginx:alpine, port 80 |
| ECR image | `078426574503.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/frontend-service` |
| Replicas (prod) | 2 (HPA: 2–5, CPU 70%) |
| Resources | req: 100m/128Mi, limit: 200m/256Mi |

**Pages:**
- `/` — Home / landing
- `/products` — Product catalog with filters
- `/products/:id` — Product detail
- `/login`, `/register` — Authentication
- `/checkout` — Checkout flow
- `/orders` — Order history

**Components of note:**
- `AIAssistant.jsx` — Floating chat widget that calls `POST /api/ai/chat`. Passes the JWT cookie automatically; the AI service uses it to unlock order-query tools for authenticated users.
- `AuthContext.jsx` — JWT stored in an HTTP-only cookie; React context reads the user from `GET /api/auth/me` on mount.
- `CartContext.jsx` — Client-side cart state (not persisted to a service).
- `axios.js` — Axios instance with `withCredentials: true` and `VITE_API_BASE_URL` base URL.

### 3.2 User Service

| Item | Detail |
|---|---|
| Technology | Node.js 20, Express, pg, bcrypt, jsonwebtoken |
| Port | 3001 |
| Database | `users_db` (PostgreSQL) |
| ECR image | `078426574503.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/user-service` |
| Replicas (prod) | 2 (HPA: 2–5, CPU 70%) |
| Resources | req: 100m/128Mi, limit: 300m/256Mi |
| IRSA role | `vastraco-production-irsa-user-service` |

**Middleware:** `helmet`, `cors`, `morgan`, `cookie-parser`

JWT tokens are signed with `JWT_SECRET` from AWS Secrets Manager and set as HTTP-only cookies with a 7-day expiry. The `secure` flag is enabled in production mode.

### 3.3 Product Service

| Item | Detail |
|---|---|
| Technology | Node.js 20, Express, pg |
| Port | 3002 |
| Database | `products_db` (PostgreSQL) |
| ECR image | `078426574503.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/product-service` |
| Replicas (prod) | 2 (HPA: 2–5, CPU 70%) |
| Resources | req: 100m/128Mi, limit: 300m/256Mi |
| IRSA role | `vastraco-production-irsa-product-service` |

Product images are served from S3 via CloudFront (`/images/*` cache behavior). The product catalog supports filtering by category, gender, occasion, material, color, price range, search text, and sort order.

### 3.4 Order Service

| Item | Detail |
|---|---|
| Technology | Node.js 20, Express, pg |
| Port | 3003 |
| Database | `orders_db` (PostgreSQL) |
| ECR image | `078426574503.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/order-service` |
| Replicas (prod) | 2 (HPA: 2–5, CPU 70%) |
| Resources | req: 100m/128Mi, limit: 300m/256Mi |
| IRSA role | `vastraco-production-irsa-order-service` |

When an order is placed, the order service calls the product service's internal stock-management endpoints (`PUT /api/products/variant/:id/stock`) within the cluster network to decrement inventory. On cancellation, stock is restored via the corresponding restore endpoint.

### 3.5 AI Service

| Item | Detail |
|---|---|
| Technology | Python 3.12, FastAPI, LangGraph, LangChain, Groq |
| Port | 3004 |
| ECR image | `078426574503.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/ai-service` |
| Replicas (prod) | 1 (HPA: 1–3, CPU 70%) |
| Resources | req: 200m/512Mi, limit: 500m/1Gi |
| IRSA role | `vastraco-production-irsa-ai-service` |
| LLM | Groq — `llama-3.3-70b-versatile` (131k context) |

**Agent Design (LangGraph ReAct):**

The agent is implemented as a LangGraph ReAct graph using `create_react_agent`. Conversation memory is held in a `MemorySaver` keyed by `session_id`, surviving across multiple turns in the same session (cleared on pod restart).

Tools are created per-request as closures that capture the product/order service URLs and the user's JWT. This allows the tool set to be extended with order-query tools when the caller is authenticated:

| Tool | Auth Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `search_products` | No | Search catalog by keyword, category, price, gender, occasion, material, color |
| `get_categories` | No | Fetch all product categories |
| `get_return_policy` | No | Return VastraCo's return/refund/exchange policy |
| `get_user_orders` | Yes (JWT) | Fetch authenticated user's order history |
| `get_order_by_id` | Yes (JWT) | Fetch a specific order by UUID |

At startup, the lifespan handler validates Groq connectivity. If validation fails, the service marks itself `degraded` via `/api/ai/health` and returns 503 on chat requests (container stays alive for log access).

JWT extraction: the route handler reads the token from the `token` HTTP-only cookie or `Authorization: Bearer` header, verifies the signature with `JWT_SECRET`, and passes the raw token to tools that forward it to the order service.

---

## 4. API Reference

### User Service (`/api/auth`)

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | None | Register a new user. Returns user object + JWT cookie |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | None | Login. Returns user object + JWT cookie |
| POST | `/api/auth/logout` | None | Clears the JWT cookie |
| GET | `/api/auth/me` | JWT | Return the current user's profile |
| PUT | `/api/auth/me` | JWT | Update the current user's display name |
| GET | `/health` | None | Liveness probe — returns `{status, service, timestamp, uptime}` |
| GET | `/ready` | None | Readiness probe — runs `SELECT 1` against the DB |

### Product Service (`/api`)

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/categories` | None | List all product categories |
| GET | `/api/products` | None | List products (supports `search`, `category`, `min_price`, `max_price`, `gender`, `occasion`, `material`, `color`, `sort`, `limit`, `offset`) |
| GET | `/api/products/:id` | None | Get product detail by ID |
| POST | `/api/products` | JWT + Admin | Create a product |
| PUT | `/api/products/:id` | JWT + Admin | Update a product |
| DELETE | `/api/products/:id` | JWT + Admin | Delete a product |
| PUT | `/api/products/variant/:id/stock` | Internal | Decrement stock (called by order-service) |
| PUT | `/api/products/variant/:id/stock/restore` | Internal | Restore stock on order cancellation |
| GET | `/health` | None | Liveness probe |
| GET | `/ready` | None | Readiness probe |

### Order Service (`/api/orders`)

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/orders` | JWT | Place a new order |
| GET | `/api/orders` | JWT | Get all orders for the authenticated user |
| GET | `/api/orders/:id` | JWT | Get a specific order by ID |
| PUT | `/api/orders/:id/cancel` | JWT | Cancel a pending order |
| GET | `/health` | None | Liveness probe |
| GET | `/ready` | None | Readiness probe |

### AI Service (`/api/ai`)

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/ai/chat` | Optional JWT | Send a message to the AI assistant. Body: `{message, session_id}`. Returns `{response, products[], session_id, authenticated}` |
| GET | `/api/ai/health` | None | Liveness probe — includes Groq connectivity status |
| GET | `/api/ai/ready` | None | Readiness probe — returns 503 if Groq is unavailable |

